Subject:[bcp] ad-hoc Ride
If you want further information about this ride PLEASE CONTACT the ride leader(s). A new ride, which is a ad-hoc/Add-on has been added to the ride list.  This is a description of the ride: 

Sun November 11, 2012 -  Winter Ride Preview  (ad-hoc ride)  meet at Valley Forge National Park - Betzwood Picnic Area (by bathrooms) (http://phillybikeclub.org/newbcp/rides/class?id=8#8 is the link for information about the start location.). The ride leaves at 9:00 am. Class B, 13.5mph, 53 or 35 miles, Preview of the upcoming Sunday winter ride from Valley Forge to Harleysville. Those that have the legs will have the option of an extra 18 mile loop through Montco, back to Harleysville, then returning to VF. (I will be riding the 35 mile route). All rest stops will have indoor/outdoor seating options at the Hennings Market.
  Cue sheets will be available. 


 Leaders:  mailto:roadrich@hotmail.com - Richard L.  Wagner - phone: 215-410-1331  

